update :

product_title: redmi note 13 pro+ 5g (fusion black, 12gb ram, 512gb storage)
all_reviews:
[{'reviewer': 'dartanian', 'rating': '1.0 ', 'date': 'reviewed in egypt on 11 july 2024', 'review': 'تجربة سيئة طبعا'}, {'reviewer': 'yassin', 'rating': '1.0 ', 'date': 'reviewed in egypt on 18 july 2024', 'review': 'كمشتري اشتريت الموبايل على اساس انه النسخه العالميه وليست الهنديه وانا شخص عايش في مصر !!!'}, {'reviewer': 'hanin el arab', 'rating': '1.0 ', 'date': 'reviewed in the united arab emirates on 2 june 2024', 'review': 'this is the indian variant, not the global.
what this will affect is having a terrible and slow network in uae. because the network bands in the phone itself are less, and they are specified for indian networks.

before you open the box, check the "model" number (not the imei or serial number). if it ends with a g, this is the global variant and would work best all around the world and in uae & gcc. if it ends with an i, then it's indian. and you better not buy it unless you live in india. and there's a last one that ends with a c, and that's the chinese variant.

there is another seller on amazon uae that sells the global variant with roughly 50 aed more. this is the one you want to get.'}, {'reviewer': 'vikramjit choudhury', 'rating': '5.0 ', 'date': 'reviewed in india on 31 august 2024', 'review': 'this is one of the best smart phones available in the market. great performance and quality.'}, {'reviewer': 'pratik kumar', 'rating': '4.0 ', 'date': 'reviewed in india on 14 july 2024', 'review': 'performance: 5/5

product_title: oppo a3 pro 5g (moonlight purple, 8gb ram, 256gb storage)|6.67” hd+ 120hz refresh rate screen | 45w supervooc|with no cost emi/additional exchange offers
all_reviews:
[{'reviewer': 'shaurya', 'rating': '5.0 ', 'date': 'reviewed in india on 1 august 2024', 'review': 'yeh phone sach mein ek all-rounder hai. performance top-notch hai aur supervooc charging se battery jaldi full charge ho jaati hai, aur poora din chalti hai bina kisi problem ke. camera quality zabardast hai, photos clear aur vibrant aati hain, aur night mode bhi kamaal ka hai. storage capacity bhi kaafi achi hai, saare photos, videos, aur apps easily store ho jaate hain. display kaafi sharp aur bright hai, aur design bhi sleek aur premium feel hota hai. overall, yeh phone ek perfect combination hai of performance, battery, camera, aur storage ka. definitely worth buying!'}, {'reviewer': 'pathikrit sur', 'rating': '5.0 ', 'date': 'reviewed in india on 23 july 2024', 'review': "i am using this mobile for two days now and i am much satisfied with it. i live in outskirts and i don't get 5g inside the house (in the extreme end of the rooms with realme 9i 5g, mind that i get full 5g in the drawing room and other rooms except the room which is very much inside) so my primary purpose was 5g inside the house, which i am getting now with oppo a3 pro. i don't do heavy gaming rather some light games and they are running fine. below i am pointing the pros and cons for others to find helpful:
pros :
1) 5g network : firstly in outskirts of west bengal you will never get jio, or voda so try airtel and airtel only. i am getting 24 hours 5g even in burrow holes. so, you will get airtel 5g in this phone.
2) battery : decent battery and even if you play mild games it must serve you one day.
3) design : it may not matter to many but the design is very eye-catching.
4) camera : decent. i will give 3/5. i am not a fan of camera.
5) sound - very loud sound.
6) very sturdy and splash proof ip 54 rating.

cons :
1) price - most important thing is it very very overpriced. market price is ₹21000. which is very costly if you ask me. i got it at ₹17k but still it is not worth it, for many people as the features are not much to speak of.
2) processor is not up to the mark as per pricing. heavy gaming will lag and may be even heat up (i didn't test it)
3) charger is not 45w - even though the charger says 45w charging but, when i checked the adapter it says 5v=2a or 9v=4.1a which means if you have low voltage it will charge slow and even if it is okay it is not 45w, but something around 40w. charged 20% to 100% in 1hour 50 minutes. there is no logo on the adapter or cord
4) hybrid sim slot - i checked in online site and did not know (my mistake though but still) so you can either have two sims or one sim and a sd card (1tb expandable).

verdict - if you can afford 2k more and don't have any reservations about better network then go for iqoo z9. it has lesser 5g bands so i bought this or else iqoo z9 is much better than this, go for it.

hay cosas que si extraño de los galaxy como la pantalla lateral y spen, pero hasta ahorita me a gustado bastante hasta estoy pensando en comprar el pixel 8 o 9 el síguete año .
lo fui a probar a un concierto y la verdad no me defraudó .'}, {'reviewer': 'yudi narine', 'rating': '5.0 ', 'date': 'reviewed in canada on 7 april 2023', 'review': "used to have a samsung s7 before. even though that phone is very old, the pixel 7 is a massive improvement in both the camera and efficiency. it has probably the best phone camera i've ever used. i regret not getting the pixel 7 pro to get the telephoto camera.

it has so many quality-of-life changes built into the phone that i would've never thought about. here's some examples:
- it has adaptive charging, which means it calculates the perfect rate to charge the phone so that it can charge to 100% before your next alarm will trigger
- even though adaptive charging is on by default, it has the option to disable it temporarily so that you can do a quick fast charge if you're in a rush
- it tells you up until what time the phone will last until with the charge left on it
- when you copy something, it has a shortcut button to paste it immediately instead of having to hold down on the screen
- taking a screenshot and cropping is so much faster

there's a bunch more qol changes that i can't think of off the top of my head. also, i realize some of these features might've been developed in earlier models, but it's still nice to have.

product_title: girasole g30-2.4-inch dual sim mobile phone - gold, earphone free, 12 months warranty
all_reviews:
[{'reviewer': 'jibreelwin', 'rating': '5.0 ', 'date': 'reviewed in egypt on 12 august 2024', 'review': 'لقد قمت مؤخراً بشراء منتج جيراسول g30، وأود أن أشارك تجربتي الرائعة معه.

1. التصميم والجودة:
من اللحظة الأولى التي استلمت فيها جيراسول g30، لاحظت الجودة العالية في التصنيع. التصميم أنيق وعصري، والمادة المستخدمة متينة وتشعر بالصلابة. التفاصيل الدقيقة في التصميم تعكس اهتمام الشركة بالجودة.

2. الأداء:
الأداء كان ممتازاً بكل المقاييس. سواء كنت أستخدم المنتج للعمل أو الترفيه، كنت دائماً مسروراً بسرعة الاستجابة والكفاءة العالية. لم أواجه أي مشكلة في الأداء حتى عند استخدامه لفترات طويلة.

3. سهولة الاستخدام:
جيراسول g30 سهل الاستخدام للغاية. الإعدادات بديهية وواضحة، مما يجعل من السهل على أي شخص البدء في استخدامه فوراً دون الحاجة إلى دليل معقد. الواجهة المستخدم سهلة التصفح وتوفر تجربة مريحة.

4. الميزات:

engineered around google tensor, google's first-ever designed processor, the pixel 6 pro proves to be the fastest and smartest pixel ever. the substantial performance leap from its predecessor is noticeable right from the get-go. it's faster, smoother, and more responsive, courtesy of its internal benchmark testing on pre-production devices, redefining user experience standards in the process.

accompanying the speedy performance is an all-day battery, intelligently crafted to cater to the most-used apps. the battery charges quickly and is remarkably adaptive, resulting in excellent power efficiency. despite extensive use of various features, including talk, data, and standby, the battery longevity was genuinely commendable, lasting an approximate 34 hours during testing.

the google pixel 6 pro's camera system is a standout feature. three pro-level lenses, including a telephoto lens with a 4x optical zoom, capture even the smallest details with stunning accuracy. the main sensor consistently takes spectacular photos in most conditions, and the telephoto lens adds an extra layer of versatility to the phone's photography abilities. furthermore, the pictures retain their high-quality resolution across platforms, like snapchat and instagram, underscoring the camera's superiority.

along with delivering robust performance, the pixel 6 pro ensures maximum security. the next-gen titan m2 chip and five years of security updates offer formidable protection for your data and privacy. switching to this device is a breeze, thanks to a simple process that quickly moves messages, contacts, and photos from your old mobile phone.

the reimagined pixel interface delivers a modern, intuitive experience, complete with colors that reflect your personal style. the display is crystal clear with good resolution, offering a comfortable viewing experience. the 120hz screen provides an incredibly smooth operation, making older 60hz phones feel outdated in comparison.

nevertheless, the pixel 6 pro isn't without its minor flaws. some users reported slightly washed-out colors compared to other phones, and the under-screen fingerprint sensor, while reliable, could be a touch faster. a feeling of hollowness when tapping the screen occasionally jars the experience. the battery, though long-lasting, could do with better optimization, and faster charging would be appreciated. a headphone jack would have been a welcome addition, but its absence is a common trend among modern smartphones.
despite these minor drawbacks, the google pixel 6 pro still manages to outshine many competitors in the market. its excellent performance, fantastic camera capabilities, robust security, modern design, and intuitive interface make it an attractive choice for android enthusiasts.

pros:

1. google tensor processor delivers excellent speed and responsiveness.
2. all-day, fast-charging battery.
3. pro-level camera system with remarkable photo quality.
4. comprehensive security with the titan m2 chip and five years of updates.
5. modern, intuitive interface with a smooth, 120hz screen.

cons:

1. slightly washed-out display colors.
2. under-screen fingerprint sensor could be faster.
3. battery optimization could be improved.
4. no headphone jack.
5. hollow feeling when tapping the screen.

in summary, the google pixel 6 pro is a stunning device that provides a fantastic blend of power, performance, and advanced features, making it a worthy addition to the android smartphone arena. on discount in july 2023 for £479, it's an investment that justifies its price tag with its top-notch capabilities and overall stellar performance.

all_reviews:
[{'reviewer': 'muhammad', 'rating': '3.0 ', 'date': 'reviewed in egypt on 29 august 2022', 'review': ', هذا التليفون يساوي بالكتير نصف تمنه, شاشة سيئة ومبكسلة, صوت رديئ, كاميرا رديئة, كل هذا بالمقارنة بالايفون اس ايه 2020, الذي يصنف فيئة اقتصادية'}, {'reviewer': 'cliente de amazon', 'rating': '5.0 ', 'date': 'reviewed in mexico on 9 september 2022', 'review': 'justo lo que esperaba, sin ningún problema hasta el momento ya con 5 meses de uso. las fotos son excelentes y el rendimiento es bastante bueno.'}, {'reviewer': 'mar', 'rating': '5.0 ', 'date': 'reviewed in spain on 2 september 2022', 'review': 'el móvil es un cañón, por 500 euros esta muy bien... cámara superior'}, {'reviewer': 'max wasserman', 'rating': '4.0 ', 'date': 'reviewed in sweden on 21 august 2022', 'review': 'this product page was unclear. the title would lead you to believe the phone was green but i recieved a coral one.

aside from that, this was an excellent purchase. the phone is really fast, with a bright and colorful display, and clean software. i wish i could customize my home screen more, like removing the google search bar but i like that the phone can color match your icons to your background image, that's cool.

i was worried about the fingerprint scanner but it works 80% of the time, even with a screen protector on (i have a glass one from "amfilm"). that may sound low but if you make sure your finger is dry when unlocking and you press down firmly, it works closer to 100%. just a bit of a hassle to line your finger up each time but you get used to it. i reccomend scanning your fingers after applying a screen protector so the phone can calibrated itself better.

the camera is great and it's fun to use. there is even a motorola style gesture for switching to the selfie cam, which is fun.

the battery life is pretty good and it has lasted me a full day of watching netflix and web browsing with music on in the background (5h of screen on time). i think keeping the brightness below 90% really helps because when it's at 100, the battery drains way faster. it was annoying to have to buy an expensive charger for fast charge when they really should have included one in the box since the phone uses a relatively new charging standard (power delivery 3.0 pps) which most chargers don't support.

additionally, i wish the software support was longer on this phone. it will only get new android versions up until winter 2024(security patches until 2026) which is a bit sad.

overall, i really like this phone.
